From: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Date: Sat, 02 May 2026 23:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ufs: exynos: gs101: release UFS PHY isolation via PMU before
 link startup [VERIFICATION]

This is a verification patch — applied on its own, with no other graft
or AOSP-shape changes, it tests the hypothesis that mainline's
gs101/gs201 HS-Rate `dl_err 0x80000002` wedge is caused by mainline
never lifting a PMU PHY-isolation gate that AOSP's vendor driver lifts
at probe.

AOSP's `private/google-modules/soc/gs/drivers/ufs/ufs-exynos.c` calls
`exynos_ufs_ctrl_phy_pwr(ufs, true)` at the top of
`exynos_ufs_config_externals()`, which walks an `ufs-phy-iso` DT
sub-node and writes its `{offset, mask, val}` triple into the PMU via
`exynos_pmu_update`. For both gs101 and gs201 (and zuma), the AOSP DT
value is:

  ufs-phy-iso {
      offset = <0x3ec8>;
      mask = <0x1>;
      val = <0x1>;
  };

i.e. write 1 to bit 0 at `pmu_alive + 0x3ec8`. Mainline's
`drivers/phy/samsung/phy-gs101-ufs.c` and
`drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c gs101_ufs_*` paths never touch the PMU.
The `samsung,pmu-syscon = <&pmu_alive>` phandle that already exists in
mainline's `phy@14704000` DT node is unused at runtime — it looks
prophylactic.

The hypothesised mechanism: bit 0 at `pmu_alive + 0x3ec8` gates the
M-PHY's analog/transmission path on the HSI2 power island. With it
cleared (presumed default at bootloader handoff), the controller can
negotiate PMC at the UIC attribute layer (which is just attribute
exchange, not data) but the PHY won't actually drive the differential
pairs in HS-Rate mode. PWM tolerates this; HS does not. That matches
the observed mainline failure exactly: PMC succeeds, host reports
FAST_MODE on both lanes, and then `dl_err 0x80000002` fires on the
first frame.

This patch adds the missing PMU write to `gs101_ufs_drv_init` (which
runs once at probe, mirroring AOSP's `exynos_ufs_config_externals`
call site). The offset 0x3ec8 is hard-coded for verification
simplicity; the eventual upstream-quality version should put the
offset/mask/val in DT to match the AOSP `ufs-phy-iso` shape.

DT-side: add `samsung,pmu-syscon = <&pmu_alive>` to the UFS node so the
driver can `syscon_regmap_lookup_by_phandle` it. The PMU node itself
already exists in mainline DT and is referenced by the PHY node.

Verification expected: HS-Rate-A or HS-Rate-B link startup completes
where it previously wedged with `dl_err 0x80000002` on the first frame
after PMC. Specifically, the kernel log should advance past
`Power mode changed to : FAST series_? G_4 L_2` *and* dispatch the
first SCSI command without a host_reset.

Test environment: Pixel Fold (felix, gs201) booted with
`kvm-arm.mode=protected` so BL31's CMU/PMU register firewalling
(see `project_pkvm_cmu_unlock.md` in the parent project) is in the
unlocked state. If the gate is BL31-firewalled at EL1 without pKVM,
the regmap_update_bits will silently no-op and HS will still wedge —
that's an additional thing this verification patch surfaces.

If verification succeeds, the upstream patch will:
  - Replace the hard-coded 0x3ec8 with a binding on the UFS node
    (likely `ufs-phy-iso { offset; mask; val; }` to match AOSP shape)
  - Add the binding to existing gs101 / gs201 / zuma DT
  - Document the binding under
    Documentation/devicetree/bindings/ufs/exynos-ufs.yaml
  - Note the BL31-firewalling-with-pKVM dependency in the patch
    cover letter so distros not running pKVM understand the
    requirement

Not for upstream as-is — this patch is a single-axis bisect tool to
validate the hypothesis. Do not apply on top of the
`feature/linux-kernel` branch's other graft work; apply on a clean
copy of `feature/linux-kernel` (or any branch that has the mainline
`drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c gs101_ufs_*` path compiled in).

Signed-off-by: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/exynos/google/gs201.dtsi |  1 +
 drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c                | 35 +++++++++++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 35 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/exynos/google/gs201.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/exynos/google/gs201.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/exynos/google/gs201.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/exynos/google/gs201.dtsi
@@ -753,6 +753,7 @@
 		 */
 		dma-coherent;
 		samsung,sysreg = <&sysreg_hsi2 0x710>;
+		samsung,pmu-syscon = <&pmu_alive>;
 	};

 	/* UFS PHY ref_clk is the 24.576 MHz SoC oscillator (gs101 uses the

diff --git a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
--- a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
+++ b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
 #include <linux/of_address.h>
 #include <linux/platform_device.h>
 #include <linux/regulator/consumer.h>
+#include <linux/mfd/syscon.h>
 #include <linux/regmap.h>
 #include <linux/phy/phy.h>

@@ -218,11 +219,43 @@ static void exynos_ufs_get_uic_info(struct exynos_ufs *ufs)
 	ufs->drv_data->uic_attr = attr;
 }

+/*
+ * VERIFICATION: lift the PMU PHY-isolation gate that AOSP's
+ * exynos_ufs_ctrl_phy_pwr() lifts at probe and that mainline currently
+ * leaves cleared. Bit 0 at pmu_alive + 0x3ec8. See cover letter for the
+ * mechanism + evidence; this is a single-axis bisect tool, not
+ * upstream-quality.
+ */
+static void gs101_ufs_release_phy_isolation(struct exynos_ufs *ufs)
+{
+	struct device *dev = ufs->dev;
+	struct regmap *pmu;
+	int ret;
+
+	pmu = syscon_regmap_lookup_by_phandle(dev->of_node,
+					      "samsung,pmu-syscon");
+	if (IS_ERR(pmu)) {
+		dev_warn(dev, "no samsung,pmu-syscon — PHY isolation not released\n");
+		return;
+	}
+
+	ret = regmap_update_bits(pmu, 0x3ec8, 0x1, 0x1);
+	if (ret)
+		dev_warn(dev, "PMU PHY-isolation write failed: %d\n", ret);
+	else
+		dev_info(dev, "PMU PHY-isolation released (offset 0x3ec8 bit 0)\n");
+}
+
 static int gs101_ufs_drv_init(struct exynos_ufs *ufs)
 {
 	struct ufs_hba *hba = ufs->hba;
 	u32 reg;

+	/*
+	 * Release PHY isolation via PMU before any link-startup activity.
+	 * Mirrors AOSP's exynos_ufs_ctrl_phy_pwr(true) at the start of
+	 * exynos_ufs_config_externals(). See gs101_ufs_release_phy_isolation
+	 * comment for the verification rationale.
+	 */
+	gs101_ufs_release_phy_isolation(ufs);
+
 	/* Enable WriteBooster */
 	hba->caps |= UFSHCD_CAP_WB_EN;

